---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Free TDEE Calculator (2026) – Calculate Your Total Daily Energy Expenditure"
  description="Calculate your Total Daily Energy Expenditure (TDEE). Find your daily calorie target based on activity."
  keywords="TDEE calculator, total daily energy expenditure, TDEE calculator online, TDEE for weight loss, TDEE for bulking, daily calorie burn, energy expenditure calculator"
  canonicalUrl="https://calbmi.com/tdee.html"
  bodyClass="brand-tdee"
>
  <Fragment slot="head">
    <script type="application/ld+json" is:inline>
    {
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "WebApplication",
      "name": "CalBmi - TDEE Calculator",
      "url": "https://calbmi.com/tdee.html",
      "description": "Calculate your Total Daily Energy Expenditure (TDEE) and BMR.",
      "applicationCategory": "HealthApplication",
      "operatingSystem": "All",
      "browserRequirements": "Requires JavaScript. Requires HTML5.",
      "offers": { "@type": "Offer", "price": "0.00", "priceCurrency": "USD" },
      "aggregateRating": {
        "@type": "AggregateRating",
        "ratingValue": "4.9",
        "ratingCount": "245",
        "bestRating": "5",
        "worstRating": "1"
      }
    }
    </script>
    <script type="application/ld+json" is:inline>
    {
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "FAQPage",
      "mainEntity": [{
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What is TDEE and how is it calculated?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "TDEE (Total Daily Energy Expenditure) is the total number of calories your body burns in a day, including your Basal Metabolic Rate (BMR) plus calories burned through physical activity, digestion, and non-exercise movement. It is calculated by multiplying your BMR by an activity factor ranging from 1.2 (sedentary) to 1.9 (super active)."
        }
      }, {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What is the difference between TDEE and BMR?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "BMR (Basal Metabolic Rate) is the number of calories your body needs at complete rest to maintain basic life functions like breathing and circulation. TDEE includes BMR plus all additional calories burned through daily activities and exercise. TDEE is always higher than BMR."
        }
      }, {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How do I use TDEE for weight loss?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "To lose weight, eat fewer calories than your TDEE. A deficit of 500 calories per day leads to approximately 0.45 kg (1 lb) of weight loss per week. A moderate deficit of 250–500 calories is recommended for sustainable, healthy weight loss without muscle loss."
        }
      }, {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How accurate is the TDEE calculator?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "The Mifflin-St Jeor equation used in this TDEE calculator is considered the most accurate formula for estimating BMR, with an accuracy of about ±10%. However, individual factors like genetics, hormones, muscle mass, and metabolic adaptation can affect your actual TDEE."
        }
      }, {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How often should I recalculate my TDEE?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "You should recalculate your TDEE every 4–6 weeks or whenever there is a significant change in your weight (more than 2–3 kg), activity level, or fitness routine. As you lose or gain weight, your calorie needs change accordingly."
        }
      }, {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What activity level should I choose?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Choose Sedentary if you have a desk job with little exercise. Lightly Active for 1–3 days of light exercise per week. Moderately Active for 3–5 days of moderate exercise. Very Active for hard exercise 6–7 days per week. Super Active if you have a physically demanding job plus intense training."
        }
      }, {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Can I use TDEE for muscle gain?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Yes. To build muscle, you need a caloric surplus above your TDEE. A lean bulk typically adds 250–500 calories above TDEE per day, combined with resistance training and adequate protein intake (1.6–2.2g per kg of body weight)."
        }
      }, {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Does TDEE change with age?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Yes. TDEE generally decreases with age because your BMR drops as you lose muscle mass and hormonal changes slow your metabolism. This is why maintaining regular exercise and adequate protein intake becomes increasingly important as you age."
        }
      }]
    }
    </script>
  </Fragment>

  <!-- Calculator Section -->
  <section id="tdee-calculator" class="calc-section" style="padding-top:2.5rem">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="calc-page-header scroll-reveal">
        <a href="/" class="back-link">
          <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><polyline points="15 18 9 12 15 6"/></svg>
          BMI Calculator
        </a>
        <div class="calc-page-title-block">
          <span class="hero-badge hero-badge-brand" style="margin:0">
            <svg width="13" height="13" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><path d="M13 2L3 14h9l-1 8 10-12h-9l1-8z"/></svg>
            Science-Based
          </span>
          <h1 class="calc-page-title">TDEE <span class="hero-gradient-brand">Calculator</span></h1>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="calc-grid">
        <!-- Input Card -->
        <div class="card calc-card scroll-reveal" style="--reveal-delay:0.05s">
          <div class="card-header">
            <h2 class="card-title">Enter Your Details</h2>
            <p class="card-subtitle">Calculate your total daily energy expenditure</p>
          </div>

          <!-- Unit Toggle -->
          <div class="unit-toggle-group" role="group" aria-label="Unit system">
            <button class="unit-btn active" id="btnMetric" onclick="setUnit('metric')">Metric</button>
            <button class="unit-btn" id="btnImperial" onclick="setUnit('imperial')">Imperial</button>
          </div>

          <form id="tdeeForm" class="bmi-form" novalidate>
            <!-- Age -->
            <div class="form-group">
              <label class="form-label" for="tdeeAge">Age <span class="label-hint">(15 – 100)</span></label>
              <div class="input-wrapper">
                <svg class="input-icon" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><circle cx="12" cy="8" r="4"/><path d="M4 20c0-4 3.58-7 8-7s8 3 8 7"/></svg>
                <input class="form-input" type="number" id="tdeeAge" placeholder="e.g. 28" min="15" max="100" />
                <span class="input-unit">yrs</span>
              </div>
              <div class="form-error" id="tdeeAgeError"></div>
            </div>

            <!-- Gender -->
            <div class="form-group">
              <label class="form-label">Gender</label>
              <div class="gender-group">
                <label class="gender-option">
                  <input type="radio" name="tdeeGender" value="male" id="tdeeGenderMale" checked />
                  <span class="gender-card">
                    <svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><circle cx="12" cy="8" r="4"/><path d="M4 20c0-4 3.58-7 8-7s8 3 8 7"/></svg>
                    Male
                  </span>
                </label>
                <label class="gender-option">
                  <input type="radio" name="tdeeGender" value="female" id="tdeeGenderFemale" />
                  <span class="gender-card">
                    <svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><circle cx="12" cy="8" r="4"/><path d="M4 20c0-4 3.58-7 8-7s8 3 8 7"/><path d="M9 20h6"/></svg>
                    Female
                  </span>
                </label>
              </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Height Metric -->
            <div class="form-group" id="tdeeHeightMetricGroup">
              <label class="form-label" for="tdeeHeightCm">Height</label>
              <div class="input-wrapper">
                <svg class="input-icon" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M12 2v20M4 6l3 3M4 12h4M4 18l3-3M20 6l-3 3M20 12h-4M20 18l-3-3"/></svg>
                <input class="form-input" type="number" id="tdeeHeightCm" placeholder="e.g. 175" min="100" max="280" />
                <span class="input-unit">cm</span>
              </div>
              <div class="form-error" id="tdeeHeightCmError"></div>
            </div>

            <!-- Height Imperial -->
            <div class="form-group hidden" id="tdeeHeightImperialGroup">
              <label class="form-label">Height</label>
              <div class="imperial-row">
                <div class="input-wrapper">
                  <svg class="input-icon" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M12 2v20"/></svg>
                  <input class="form-input" type="number" id="tdeeHeightFt" placeholder="5" min="1" max="9" />
                  <span class="input-unit">ft</span>
                </div>
                <div class="input-wrapper">
                  <input class="form-input" type="number" id="tdeeHeightIn" placeholder="9" min="0" max="11" />
                  <span class="input-unit">in</span>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="form-error" id="tdeeHeightImperialError"></div>
            </div>

            <!-- Weight Metric -->
            <div class="form-group" id="tdeeWeightMetricGroup">
              <label class="form-label" for="tdeeWeightKg">Weight</label>
              <div class="input-wrapper">
                <svg class="input-icon" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M12 3a3 3 0 0 1 3 3H9a3 3 0 0 1 3-3z"/><rect x="3" y="6" width="18" height="15" rx="2"/></svg>
                <input class="form-input" type="number" id="tdeeWeightKg" placeholder="e.g. 70" min="30" max="600" step="0.1" />
                <span class="input-unit">kg</span>
              </div>
              <div class="form-error" id="tdeeWeightKgError"></div>
            </div>

            <!-- Weight Imperial -->
            <div class="form-group hidden" id="tdeeWeightImperialGroup">
              <label class="form-label" for="tdeeWeightLbs">Weight</label>
              <div class="input-wrapper">
                <svg class="input-icon" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M12 3a3 3 0 0 1 3 3H9a3 3 0 0 1 3-3z"/><rect x="3" y="6" width="18" height="15" rx="2"/></svg>
                <input class="form-input" type="number" id="tdeeWeightLbs" placeholder="e.g. 154" min="66" max="1300" step="0.1" />
                <span class="input-unit">lbs</span>
              </div>
              <div class="form-error" id="tdeeWeightLbsError"></div>
            </div>

            <!-- Activity Level -->
            <div class="form-group">
              <label class="form-label">Activity Level</label>
              <div class="activity-grid">
                <label class="activity-option">
                  <input type="radio" name="tdeeActivity" value="1.2" id="tdeeSedentary" checked />
                  <span class="activity-card">
                    <span class="activity-dot"></span>
                    <span class="activity-text">
                      <span class="activity-name">Sedentary</span>
                      <span class="activity-desc">Little or no exercise, desk job</span>
                    </span>
                    <span class="activity-mult">×1.2</span>
                  </span>
                </label>
                <label class="activity-option">
                  <input type="radio" name="tdeeActivity" value="1.375" id="tdeeLight" />
                  <span class="activity-card">
                    <span class="activity-dot"></span>
                    <span class="activity-text">
                      <span class="activity-name">Lightly Active</span>
                      <span class="activity-desc">Light exercise 1–3 days/week</span>
                    </span>
                    <span class="activity-mult">×1.375</span>
                  </span>
                </label>
                <label class="activity-option">
                  <input type="radio" name="tdeeActivity" value="1.55" id="tdeeModerate" />
                  <span class="activity-card">
                    <span class="activity-dot"></span>
                    <span class="activity-text">
                      <span class="activity-name">Moderately Active</span>
                      <span class="activity-desc">Moderate exercise 3–5 days/week</span>
                    </span>
                    <span class="activity-mult">×1.55</span>
                  </span>
                </label>
                <label class="activity-option">
                  <input type="radio" name="tdeeActivity" value="1.725" id="tdeeVery" />
                  <span class="activity-card">
                    <span class="activity-dot"></span>
                    <span class="activity-text">
                      <span class="activity-name">Very Active</span>
                      <span class="activity-desc">Hard exercise 6–7 days/week</span>
                    </span>
                    <span class="activity-mult">×1.725</span>
                  </span>
                </label>
                <label class="activity-option">
                  <input type="radio" name="tdeeActivity" value="1.9" id="tdeeSuper" />
                  <span class="activity-card">
                    <span class="activity-dot"></span>
                    <span class="activity-text">
                      <span class="activity-name">Super Active</span>
                      <span class="activity-desc">Physical job + hard exercise daily</span>
                    </span>
                    <span class="activity-mult">×1.9</span>
                  </span>
                </label>
              </div>
            </div>

            <button type="submit" class="calc-btn-brand" id="tdeeCalcBtn">
              <svg width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><path d="M13 2L3 14h9l-1 8 10-12h-9l1-8z"/></svg>
              Calculate TDEE
            </button>

            <button type="button" class="reset-btn" onclick="resetTdeeForm()">
              <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M3 12a9 9 0 1 0 9-9 9.75 9.75 0 0 0-6.74 2.74L3 8"/><path d="M3 3v5h5"/></svg>
              Reset
            </button>
          </form>
        </div>

        <!-- Result Card -->
        <div class="card calc-card scroll-reveal" style="--reveal-delay:0.15s" id="tdeeResultCard">
          <div class="cal-placeholder" id="tdeePlaceholder">
            <div class="cal-placeholder-icon" style="background:rgba(16,185,129,0.08);color:#10b981">⚡</div>
            <p class="placeholder-text">Enter your details and click <strong>Calculate TDEE</strong> to see your daily energy expenditure</p>
          </div>

          <div class="cal-result-section hidden fade-in-up" id="tdeeResultContent">
            <!-- TDEE Hero -->
            <div class="result-hero">
              <div class="result-hero-label">Your Total Daily Energy Expenditure</div>
              <div class="result-hero-value" id="tdeeValue">–</div>
              <div class="result-hero-unit">kcal / day</div>
            </div>

            <!-- BMR Info -->
            <div class="bmr-info">
              <span class="bmr-info-label">🫀 Basal Metabolic Rate (BMR)</span>
              <span class="bmr-info-value" id="tdeeBmrValue">–</span>
            </div>

            <!-- Calorie Targets -->
            <div>
              <h3 class="section-title" style="margin-bottom:0.75rem">Calorie Targets by Goal</h3>
              <div class="goal-strip" id="tdeeGoalStrip"></div>
            </div>

            <!-- Activity Level Breakdown -->
            <div>
              <h3 class="section-title" style="margin-bottom:0.75rem">TDEE at Each Activity Level</h3>
              <div class="table-wrapper">
                <table class="activity-level-table" id="tdeeActivityTable"></table>
              </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Macros -->
            <div class="macro-section">
              <h3 class="macro-title">Recommended Macronutrients (Maintenance)</h3>
              <div class="macro-bars">
                <div class="macro-row">
                  <span class="macro-name">Protein</span>
                  <div class="macro-bar-track"><div class="macro-bar-fill protein" id="tdeeBarProtein"></div></div>
                  <span class="macro-pct" id="tdeePctProtein"></span>
                  <span class="macro-grams" id="tdeeGProtein"></span>
                </div>
                <div class="macro-row">
                  <span class="macro-name">Carbs</span>
                  <div class="macro-bar-track"><div class="macro-bar-fill carbs" id="tdeeBarCarbs"></div></div>
                  <span class="macro-pct" id="tdeePctCarbs"></span>
                  <span class="macro-grams" id="tdeeGCarbs"></span>
                </div>
                <div class="macro-row">
                  <span class="macro-name">Fat</span>
                  <div class="macro-bar-track"><div class="macro-bar-fill fat" id="tdeeBarFat"></div></div>
                  <span class="macro-pct" id="tdeePctFat"></span>
                  <span class="macro-grams" id="tdeeGFat"></span>
                </div>
              </div>
              <p style="font-size:0.75rem;color:var(--muted-foreground);margin-top:0.25rem">
                Based on 30% protein, 40% carbs, 30% fat of maintenance calories.
              </p>
            </div>

            <!-- Health tip -->
            <div class="health-message" id="tdeeHealthMsg"></div>

            <!-- Macros CTA -->
            <div class="calories-cta" id="macroCta" style="margin-top: 1.25rem;">
              <div class="cta-icon">
                <svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M21.21 15.89A10 10 0 1 1 8 2.83"/><path d="M22 12A10 10 0 0 0 12 2v10z"/></svg>
              </div>
              <div class="cta-body">
                <p class="cta-title">Calculate your macro targets</p>
                <p class="cta-sub">Find the perfect balance of protein, carbs, and fats to meet your daily energy needs.</p>
              </div>
              <a href="/macro.html" class="cta-btn" id="macroCtaBtn">
                Find Macros
                <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><polyline points="9 18 15 12 9 6"/></svg>
              </a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Info Section -->
      <div class="section-header scroll-reveal" style="margin-top:4.5rem;margin-bottom:2.5rem">
        <div class="section-badge" style="background:rgba(16,185,129,0.1);color:#10b981;border-color:rgba(16,185,129,0.2)">Learn More</div>
        <h2 class="section-title-lg">Understanding TDEE & Energy Expenditure</h2>
        <p class="section-description" style="max-width:640px;margin:0.5rem auto 0;color:var(--muted-foreground)">Learn the science behind total daily energy expenditure and how to use it for your fitness goals.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="info-grid scroll-reveal" style="margin-top:1.5rem;--reveal-delay:0.1s">
        <div class="info-card">
          <div class="info-icon" style="background:rgba(16,185,129,0.1);color:#10b981">
            <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M13 2L3 14h9l-1 8 10-12h-9l1-8z"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="info-title">What is TDEE?</h3>
          <p class="info-text">Total Daily Energy Expenditure is the total number of calories your body burns in a 24-hour period — including BMR, physical activity, digestion, and non-exercise movement.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="info-card">
          <div class="info-icon" style="background:rgba(99,102,241,0.1);color:#6366f1">
            <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M20.84 4.61a5.5 5.5 0 0 0-7.78 0L12 5.67l-1.06-1.06a5.5 5.5 0 0 0-7.78 7.78l1.06 1.06L12 21.23l7.78-7.78 1.06-1.06a5.5 5.5 0 0 0 0-7.78z"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="info-title">TDEE vs BMR</h3>
          <p class="info-text">BMR is your body's calorie needs at complete rest. TDEE adds your physical activity on top. For most people, TDEE is 1.3x–1.9x their BMR depending on lifestyle.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="info-card">
          <div class="info-icon" style="background:rgba(249,115,22,0.1);color:#f97316">
            <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><polyline points="22 12 18 12 15 21 9 3 6 12 2 12"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="info-title">Mifflin-St Jeor Formula</h3>
          <p class="info-text">This calculator uses the Mifflin-St Jeor equation, widely considered the most accurate method for estimating BMR. It is recommended by the American Dietetic Association.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="info-card">
          <div class="info-icon" style="background:rgba(236,72,153,0.1);color:#ec4899">
            <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><rect x="3" y="3" width="18" height="18" rx="2"/><path d="M3 9h18M9 21V9"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="info-title">Using TDEE for Goals</h3>
          <p class="info-text">Eat below TDEE to lose fat. Eat at TDEE to maintain. Eat above TDEE to gain muscle. A 500-calorie daily deficit equals roughly 0.45 kg of fat loss per week.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- SEO Content -->
  <section class="seo-guide-section scroll-reveal">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="seo-article-main">
        <h2>The Complete Guide to TDEE: Total Daily Energy Expenditure Explained</h2>
        <p>Understanding your <strong>TDEE (Total Daily Energy Expenditure)</strong> is the cornerstone of any successful nutrition strategy — whether your goal is losing fat, maintaining weight, or building lean muscle mass. Unlike simple calorie counting that relies on generic recommendations, TDEE gives you a personalized daily calorie target based on your unique body composition, age, gender, and actual activity level. This comprehensive <strong>TDEE calculator</strong> uses the Mifflin-St Jeor equation, which research has consistently shown to be the most accurate predictive formula for estimating basal metabolic rate in healthy adults.</p>

        <h3>How TDEE Is Calculated: The Science Behind the Numbers</h3>
        <p>Your total daily energy expenditure is composed of several distinct components. The largest component, accounting for 60–75% of your daily burn, is your <strong>Basal Metabolic Rate (BMR)</strong> — the energy your body requires simply to stay alive while completely at rest. This includes breathing, circulating blood, maintaining body temperature, and cellular repair. The second component is the <strong>Thermic Effect of Food (TEF)</strong>, which represents the calories burned during digestion (typically 10% of intake). The third component is <strong>physical activity</strong>, which can range from 15–30% of total expenditure depending on your lifestyle. Finally, <strong>Non-Exercise Activity Thermogenesis (NEAT)</strong> — fidgeting, walking, standing, and other daily movements — can account for a surprising 100–800 calories per day.</p>

        <h3>Understanding Activity Multipliers</h3>
        <p>The activity multiplier is a critical factor in your TDEE calculation. Choosing the right level ensures your calorie target is accurate. <strong>Sedentary (×1.2)</strong> applies to individuals with desk jobs who perform minimal exercise — perhaps a short walk or household chores. <strong>Lightly Active (×1.375)</strong> fits those who exercise 1–3 times per week at low intensity, such as yoga, walking, or light cycling. <strong>Moderately Active (×1.55)</strong> is appropriate for people who train 3–5 days with moderate intensity — typical gym-goers who combine cardio and resistance training. <strong>Very Active (×1.725)</strong> describes athletes or individuals who train hard 6–7 days per week. <strong>Super Active (×1.9)</strong> is reserved for people with physically demanding occupations (construction workers, professional athletes) who also train intensely.</p>

        <h3>Using TDEE for Weight Loss</h3>
        <p>The principle behind weight loss is straightforward: create a caloric deficit by consuming fewer calories than your TDEE. A <strong>moderate deficit of 500 calories per day</strong> will result in approximately 0.45 kg (1 pound) of weight loss per week, which is considered a safe and sustainable rate. Aggressive deficits of 750–1000 calories may accelerate fat loss initially but come with increased risk of muscle loss, metabolic adaptation, nutrient deficiencies, and eventual diet burnout. For most individuals, eating at 80–85% of TDEE provides an optimal balance between fat loss speed and long-term sustainability.</p>

        <h3>Using TDEE for Muscle Gain</h3>
        <p>Building muscle requires a caloric surplus above your TDEE. A <strong>lean bulk</strong> typically involves eating 250–500 calories above maintenance, which supports muscle growth while minimizing unnecessary fat gain. Combined with progressive resistance training and adequate protein intake (1.6–2.2 grams per kilogram of body weight), this approach enables quality weight gain of approximately 0.25–0.5 kg per week for intermediate lifters. More aggressive surpluses can be appropriate for beginners or those recovering from extended deficits.</p>

        <h3>TDEE and Macronutrient Distribution</h3>
        <p>Once you know your TDEE, the next step is distributing those calories across the three macronutrients: protein, carbohydrates, and fats. A balanced starting point is the <strong>30/40/30 split</strong> — 30% protein, 40% carbs, 30% fat. This provides sufficient protein for muscle maintenance and recovery, adequate carbohydrates for energy and training performance, and enough dietary fat for hormonal health and nutrient absorption. However, these ratios should be adjusted based on individual preferences, training style, and specific goals.</p>

        <h3>Common Mistakes When Using TDEE</h3>
        <p>One of the most frequent errors is <strong>overestimating activity level</strong>. Many people select "Very Active" when they should be choosing "Lightly Active" or "Moderately Active." Be honest about your actual exercise frequency and intensity. Another common mistake is failing to recalculate TDEE as your body changes — as you lose weight, your TDEE decreases, meaning the same calorie intake that initially created a deficit may eventually become maintenance. Finally, remember that TDEE is an <strong>estimate</strong>, not an exact number. Track your weight trends over 2–3 weeks and adjust intake by 100–200 calories if your weight isn't moving in the desired direction.</p>

        <p>By understanding and utilizing your TDEE effectively, you gain the most powerful tool available for managing body composition. Whether you are using this <strong>TDEE calculator</strong> for the first time or recalculating after a training phase, remember that consistency in tracking and patience with results are what ultimately determine success. Pair this tool with our <a href="/">BMI Calculator</a> for a comprehensive health assessment, or explore our <a href="/calories.html">Calorie Calculator</a> for detailed meal planning guidance.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FAQ Section -->
  <section id="faq" class="faq-section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <div class="section-badge" style="background:rgba(16,185,129,0.1);color:#10b981;border-color:rgba(16,185,129,0.2)">FAQ</div>
        <h2 class="section-title-lg">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-list scroll-reveal" style="--reveal-delay:0.05s">
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)" aria-expanded="false">
            What is TDEE and how is it calculated?
            <svg class="faq-arrow" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>TDEE (Total Daily Energy Expenditure) is the total calories your body burns daily. It's calculated by first determining your BMR (Basal Metabolic Rate) using the Mifflin-St Jeor equation, then multiplying by an activity factor (1.2–1.9) based on your lifestyle.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)" aria-expanded="false">
            What is the difference between TDEE and BMR?
            <svg class="faq-arrow" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>BMR is the calories your body needs at complete rest — just to breathe, circulate blood, and maintain organs. TDEE is BMR plus all calories burned through daily movement, exercise, and digestion. TDEE is always higher than BMR.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)" aria-expanded="false">
            How do I use TDEE for weight loss?
            <svg class="faq-arrow" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>To lose weight, eat fewer calories than your TDEE. A deficit of 500 calories per day leads to approximately 0.45 kg (1 lb) of weight loss per week. A moderate deficit of 250–500 calories is best for sustainable, healthy fat loss.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)" aria-expanded="false">
            How accurate is the TDEE calculator?
            <svg class="faq-arrow" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>The Mifflin-St Jeor equation is considered the most accurate BMR formula, within approximately ±10%. However, individual factors like genetics, hormones, metabolic adaptation, and body composition can affect your actual TDEE. Track your weight for 2–3 weeks and adjust accordingly.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)" aria-expanded="false">
            How often should I recalculate my TDEE?
            <svg class="faq-arrow" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>Recalculate every 4–6 weeks, or whenever you gain or lose more than 2–3 kg, change your exercise routine significantly, or notice your weight plateau despite consistent intake.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)" aria-expanded="false">
            Can I use TDEE for muscle gain and bulking?
            <svg class="faq-arrow" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>Yes! For a lean bulk, eat 250–500 calories above your TDEE daily. Pair with resistance training and 1.6–2.2g of protein per kg of body weight. This approach supports muscle growth while minimizing unnecessary fat gain.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

